TextEng: Save your posturing. Just show me what you have.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> How will you know if you don't show me? Come on.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 보여주지 않으면 알 수 없지. 어서.

TextEng: That is an insane price! There must be a cheaper way!
Text: 미친 가격이군! 더 싼 방법이 있어야지!

TextEng: Where can I get more if I need them?
Text: 더 필요하면 어디서 더 구할 수 있지?

TextEng: Very well, I will purchase three.
Very well, I will purchase two.
Very well, I will purchase one.
Thank you for your time, then.
Just show me your standard fare.
Of course. Have you got anything interesting?
Another time. Goodbye
What you got? Anything good?
Shut up and show what you have.
Just show me normal stuff.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Maybe you show and me decide. Come on.
Maybe later. Bye.
Bye then.
Me buy one.
Me buy two.
Me buy three.
Where can me get more?
That too much! Can they be cheaper?
Text: 너무 비싸! 더 싸게 안 돼?

TextEng: Well, in case I want to do that, where is the Seedy Tavern?
Text: 좋아, 그렇게 하려면 시디 선술집은 어디지?

TextEng: Whatever. So, where Seedy Tavern at?
